	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Gargoyles are easily beatable by necromancers from level 16 onwards.  By this level you should have some decent stuff boosting INT/mana.  I think I had an intelligence of about 150 at 16 with about 50 extra mana from items.. so to be safe try and be around there.<BR>
<BR>
Here is what you do... kill the skeletons to start the spawn.  I usually kill 3 or 4 (meleeing with vampiric embrace along with pet for fun).  Once you do this, go to the little peak that is furthest away from the temple with spectres.  Always med up there as mobs won't go that way.  I try and have about 4 bubbles when fighting to be safe.<BR>
<BR>
Be sure you have a pet that is level 15 or 16 (hitting for 18-20) and cast Spirit Armor on it.  Pull a gargoyle with Engulfing Darkness back towards the med spot.  When he's almost to you sick the pet on him.  As soon as pet engages, cast Heat Blood.  IMMEDIATELY follow up with Heart Flutter. This is important since you want the gargoyle chasing you.  Proceed to kite around the shore of the island constantly checking to make sure the gargoyle is after you and not on your pet.  If it ever stops chasing you, turn, cast Lifedraw once or twice and run into melee casting lifedraw the whole time.  Now you're just tanking for your pet, which it WILL obliterate pet if you're not careful.  If your pet ever dies and the gargoyle isn't on the verge of fleeing, feign death.  You won't win.  If you ever pull more than one, feign death.  <BR>
<BR>
Good luck. It is GREAT xp.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
